{
  "stem": "10768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Approximately from the 1st of September, probably until maybe the third week in September, I came back to Oswiecim.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I came back, of course, since the store was in Katowice, our-- the owner of the store, which was our cousin, he-- since he was a bearded man, a, a man with a-- a Jew with a beard and with, with Orthodox attire-- so of course, I was the one who went back.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His children-- his oldest daughter was four years younger than I was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was too young to do anything to help them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I went back to Katowice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was in Katowice September, October, November-- September-- the end of September-- September, October, November.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "During that time in Katowice was a Jewish committee, which was on the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was the Jewish-- this was their building from before the war, too.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They have made, like, a soup kitchen for the people who couldn't get food.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were coordinating a lot of things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "During that period of time was the first deportation of all able young Jewish men.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They took them together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the Jewish committee gave a request that whoever has stores with clothing or with shovels or anything like that, that these stores should provide these things voluntarily.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If they will not give voluntarily, the Germans will just break the, the lock and go in and get whatever they need.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I was at that time there, too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And since it was a clothing store, I provided some of the clothing for the men.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "During that deportation, none of the wife or children knew where the men were going.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Germans said that they are going somewhere to a labor, labor place-- place of labor-- that they will work there.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
